One in three of women worldwide have experienced either physical and/or sexual intimate partner violence or non-partner sexual violence in their lifetime.
The brutal state violence being employed against them is emblematic of the violent nature of capitalism and imperialism itself.
This is an example of capitalist state violence employed to protect the status quo.
Build the international socialist feminist struggleIn the run up to November 25 in which major demonstrations against gender violence will take place in many countries around the world, we will publish articles from a number of our sections about the struggle against gender violence.
Build for mass demonstrations on November 25 against gender violence as a step towards building mass protests and mass strikes internationally on March 8, 2020.